questions.query: Telegram Handle We Can Use To Contact You
Link to your Public Group Chat
Have you participated in a previous Gitcoin Grants Round? If so, please name the rounds or link the builder profile to prior rounds.
How does your project contribute significantly to the Ethereum network's infrastructure? Please provide specific examples and metrics if available.
questions.explanation:
* Helping onboard new staking operators with 1-click node installer, called EthPillar, increasing Ethereum's resilience and decentralization.

* Blocks created by EthPillar and the staking guides can be seen by tracking graffiti at: https://beaconcha.in/slots?q=%F0%9F%8F%A0%F0%9F%A5%A9%F0%9F%AA%99%F0%9F%9B%A1

* This OG staking guide since beacon chain's genesis helped seed the first beach chain block (created by Mr. F), and inspired projects you might know such as Lido, RocketPool, theDailyGwei.

questions.query: Describe any pioneering development work in your project, particularly in enhancing privacy, interoperability, or user experience.
questions.explanation: EthPillar's 1-click 1-line script is the fastest way to deploy a full node or staking node with validator keys. EthPillar's rapid turnaround time and pioneering integration was available for the recent Hoodi Testnet launch pre-genesis, enabling even beginneers to join on slot 0.

questions.query: What specific problems or challenges in the Ethereum ecosystem does your project address? How does your solution improve upon existing alternatives?
questions.explanation: Make Ethereum solo-staking fun and not too technical.

questions.query: Outline your project's roadmap and how the grant funds will be used to achieve your development goals.
questions.explanation: Motivation to support Pectra and the upcoming future Glamsterdam forks. Roadmap includes implementing  features a home solo staker would find useful.

questions.query: How does your project contribute to the decentralization and security of the Ethereum network?
questions.explanation:
Increases node count.
Lowers the technical barrier to staking.
Lowers the financial requirement to staking.
Decreases risk of non-finality event by supporting minority execution-consensus layer clients. 
Builds and supports the Ethereum home solo staking community.
